features.name: Alar Base Junction/Alar Crease - left
features.description: The junction between the left alar crease and the cheek.

features.name: Alar Base Junction/Alar Crease - right
features.description: The junction between the right alar crease and the cheek.

features.name: Alar Rim’s Highest Point - left
features.description: The highest point of the left alar rim.

features.name: Alar Rim’s Highest Point - right
features.description: The highest point of the right alar rim.

features.name: Alare/Alar Flare - left
features.description: The most lateral point on the ala of the nose. The point where the nasal blade (ala nasi) extends farthest out. The most lateral point on each alar contour.

features.name: Alare/Alar Flare - right
features.description: The most lateral point on the ala of the nose. The point where the nasal blade (ala nasi) extends farthest out. The most lateral point on each alar contour.

features.name: Anterior Point of Nostril/Columella Junction left
features.description: The point where the left ala meets the upper end of the columella.

features.name: Anterior Point of Nostril/Columella Junction right
features.description: The point where the right ala meets the upper end of the columella.

features.name: Cheilion - left
features.description: The most lateral point on left side of the gently closed lips. A bilateral landmark located at the outermost corner (commissure) of the mouth where the upper and lower lips meet.

features.name: Cheilion - right
features.description: The most lateral point on right side of the gently closed lips. A bilateral landmark located at the outermost corner (commissure) of the mouth where the upper and lower lips meet.

features.name: Columellar Break Point
features.description: The most anterior or the highest point on the columella crest at the apex of the nostril. The point in the columellar region of the nose where the tip of the nose stops curving and the columellar linear structure begins, in the midline.

features.name: Endocanthion/Medial Canthus - left
features.description: The inner corner of the left eye where the upper and lower eyelids meet. The point at the inner commissure of the eye fissure.

features.name: Endocanthion/Medial Canthus - right
features.description: The inner corner of the right eye where the upper and lower eyelids meet. The point at the inner commissure of the eye fissure.

features.name: Exocanthion/Lateral Canthus - left
features.description: The outer corner of the left eye where the upper and lower eyelids meet. The point at the outer commissure of the eye fissure.

features.name: Exocanthion/Lateral Canthus - right
features.description: The outer corner of the right eye where the upper and lower eyelids meet. The point at the outer commissure of the eye fissure.

features.name: Glabella
features.description: The most prominent point of the forehead in the midline between the eyebrows.

features.name: Labrale Superius
features.description: The midpoint on the vermilion line of the upper lip. Located in the midline - between the philtral ridges - along the vermillion border of the upper lip.

features.name: Maxilloanteriorale - left
features.description: The point where the left maxilloanterioral and nasoanterioral sutures meet. The soft tissue points located at each lateral margin of the base of the nasal root at the level of the endocanthion. At the base of the nasal root medially from each endocanthion.

features.name: Maxilloanteriorale - right
features.description: The point where the right maxilloanterioral and nasoanterioral sutures meet. The soft tissue points located at each lateral margin of the base of the nasal root at the level of the endocanthion. At the base of the nasal root medially from each endocanthion.

features.name: Midpoint of left Infraorbital Rim
features.description: The midpoint of the left infraorbital rim. This is only used for the equation of the Frankfort Horizontal Plane.

features.name: Midpoint of right Infraorbital Rim
features.description: The midpoint of the right infraorbital rim. This is only used for the equation of the Frankfort Horizontal Plane.

features.name: Most Prominent Point of Convexity
features.description: The most prominent point of convexity on the nose. This feature point is for the calculation of the degree of deviation in C-type nasal deformities.

features.name: Nasal Parenthesis - left
features.description: The summit of the left nasal parentheses/canthal-alar line.

features.name: Nasal Parenthesis - right
features.description: The summit of the right nasal parentheses/canthal-alar line.

features.name: Nasion/Radix
features.description: Nasion is the deepest point of the nasofrontal groove. The deepest point on the bridge of the nose overlying the centre of the suture between the nasal and frontal bones. The point in the midline of both the nasal root and the nasofrontal suture.

features.name: Pogonion
features.description: Most anterior point on the soft tissue profile of the chin in mid-sagittal plane.

features.name: Posterior Point of Nostril - left
features.description: The point where the left ala meets the nostril floor at a point corresponding to sbal.

features.name: Posterior Point of Nostril - right
features.description: The point where the right ala meets the nostril floor at a point corresponding to sbal.

features.name: Pronasale/Tip
features.description: The most prominent point of the nasal tip. Point of maximum anterior projection of the nose on the lateral view at the tip region. The most protrusive point on the nasal tip in the midline.

features.name: Stomion
features.description: Point at which the upper and lower lip make contact. Located along the labial fissure in the midline.

features.name: Subalare - left
features.description: The point at the lower limit of each alar base, where the alar base disappears into skin of the upper lip. A bilateral landmark located below the nostril opening at the point where the infero-medial continuation of the alar cartilage inserts into the skin of the upper lip.

features.name: Subalare - right
features.description: The point at the lower limit of each alar base, where the alar base disappears into skin of the upper lip. A bilateral landmark located below the nostril opening at the point where the infero-medial continuation of the alar cartilage inserts into the skin of the upper lip.

features.name: Sublabiale/Mentolabial Sulcus
features.description: The deepest point of the lower border of the lower lip or the upper border of the chin. Located at the midpoint of the labiomental groove or sulcus.

features.name: Subnasale - left
features.description: Indicates the midpoint of the left columella crest where the thickness of the columella (sn'-sn') is measured.

features.name: Subnasale - right
features.description: Indicates the midpoint of the right columella crest where the thickness of the columella (sn'-sn') is measured.

features.name: Subnasale
features.description: The midpoint of the columella base. The deepest point at the junction of the base of the columella and the upper lip in the midline. Located at the apex of the nasolabial angle in the midline, where the inferior border of the nasal septum meets the skin of the upper lip.

features.name: Supratarsal Crease - left
features.description: The left supratarsal crease's intersection with the nasal bridge.

features.name: Supratarsal Crease - right
features.description: The right supratarsal crease's intersection with the nasal bridge.

features.name: Supratip Break Point
features.description: According to ideals, “Tip-defining points should project approximately 6 to 10 mm over the nasal dorsum in female patients.” Is one of the common referring points, hence marking the supra tip breaking point where tip elevation starts from the dorsum. The nasal region where the inferior region of the nasal dorsum meets the tip of the nose. Tip defining points, supratip break point, and the columellar-lobular angle. Primary supratip deformity is characterized by an underprojected supratip, an overprojected tip, and a cephalic-oriented lower lateral cartilage. A secondary supratip deformity is caused by supratip soft tissue excess, an overresected supratip, residual excess in the caudal dorsum, inadequate tip projection, and a residual, excessive septum of the supratip and underprojected tip. The balance between the nasal dorsum and the tip-defining points is scrutinized to control the supratip break. Tip-defining points should project approximately 6 to 10 mm over the nasal dorsum in female patients.

features.name: Tip Defining Point - left
features.description: The nasal tip defining point (TDP) is the most anterior projection of the tip cartilages, usually corresponding to the apex of the lobular arch anatomically, and is typically identified externally where the light reflex is seen on the nasal tip.

features.name: Tip Defining Point - right
features.description: The nasal tip defining point (TDP) is the most anterior projection of the tip cartilages, usually corresponding to the apex of the lobular arch anatomically, and is typically identified externally where the light reflex is seen on the nasal tip.

features.name: Tragion - left
features.description: The notch on the upper margin of the left tragus. A bilateral landmark located within the small notch at the superior extent of the tragus (cartilaginous projection just anterior to the auditory meatus), where the cartilage meets the face.

features.name: Tragion - right
features.description: The notch on the upper margin of the right tragus. A bilateral landmark located within the small notch at the superior extent of the tragus (cartilaginous projection just anterior to the auditory meatus), where the cartilage meets the face.

features.name: Trichion
features.description: The point on the hairline in the midline of the forehead.

features.name: Vertex
features.description: The topmost point of the vault of the cranium.

features.name: Zygion - left
features.description: The most lateral point of left zygomatic arch.

features.name: Zygion - right
features.description: The most lateral point of right zygomatic arch.

measurements.name: Alar Base Width
measurements.description: Distance from 'Alar Curvature/Alar Base Junction - left (ac_l)' to 'Alar Curvature/Alar Base Junction - right (ac_r)'

measurements.name: Alar Base Width - Surface
measurements.description: Distance from 'Alar Curvature/Alar Base Junction - left (ac_l)' to 'Alar Curvature/Alar Base Junction - right (ac_r)'

measurements.name: Interalar Distance
measurements.description: Distance between 'Alare/Alar Flare - left (al_l)' and 'Alar/Alar Flare - right (al_r)'

measurements.name: Interalar Distance - Surface
measurements.description: Distance between 'Alare/Alar Flare - left (al_l)' and 'Alar/Alar Flare - right (al_r)'

measurements.name: Interalar Angle
measurements.description: Angle between 'Alare - left (al_l)' to 'Pronasale/Tip (prn)' and 'Pronasale/Tip (prn)' to Alare - right (al_r))' Formed near the nose tip by the two tangents touching the alar on either side. Used to classify the nose shape into different morphological types.

measurements.name: Nasal Tip Angle
measurements.description: The angle between 'Nasion (n)' to 'Pronasale/Tip (prn)' and 'Pronasale/Tip (prn)' to 'Subnasale (sn)'

measurements.name: Nasofrontal Angle
measurements.description: The angle between 'Glabella (g)' to 'Nasion (n)' and 'Nasion (n)' to 'Pronasale/Tip (prn)'

measurements.name: Nasolabial Angle 1
measurements.description: The angle between 'Pronasale/Tip (prn)' to 'Subnasale (sn)' and 'Subnasale (sn)' to 'Labrale Superius (ls)'

measurements.name: Nasal Tip Projection: Goode
measurements.description: The distance from Pronasale  (prn) to Alar Base Junction/Alar Crease - right (ac r) divided by the distance from Nasion (n) to Nasal Tip/Pronasale (prn).

measurements.name: Nasal Width-Length Ratio
measurements.description: The alar width divided by the nasal bridge length. Nasal width (ala to ala) divided by the length of the nose (nasion to pronasion)
